    <body>
        <p>You can filter your Flare projects by one or more targets. The resulting project will include all of the translatable files that are part of the selected target(s), such as topics, images, skins, and variables.</p>
        <p>A good reason to use target filters is if you need to maintain different translations for different targets. Additionally, you could filter to a specific target and use variable flattening<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineOnly,Snippets.Snippet11"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Lingo/Introduction/Whats-New-Lingo.htm#Flattening">Snippet and Variable Flattening</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet10,General.OnlineOnly"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Lingo/Filters/Content-Flattening.htm">Content Flattening</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText> if you need use different definitions of a variable in different targets.</p>
    </body>
